description:
The aim of this work was&nbsp;to develop a calibration procedure to cover the production of static and continuous&nbsp; 
forces by industrial machines, used for both materials testing and in the larger scale testing of components,&nbsp; 
products, and structures &ndash; this second application&nbsp;incorporated the use of multiple force sensors, reversal&nbsp; 
of loading direction, and novel transducer design.&nbsp; 

 The calibration procedure can be generally used without any limit of the nominal load range, so the typical force range for material tests from 1 N to 1 MN can be served.&nbsp;

